    <h1>Motion</h1>
    <p class="text-l color-neutral-600">Duration and easing tokens for consistent, accessible animation. All durations automatically collapse to 0 ms when the user has enabled "reduce motion" at the OS level.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2 class="heading-l">Duration tokens</h2>
    <p>Five named durations from near-instant micro-feedback to slow deliberate reveals. Use faster durations for small, frequent interactions (hover states, focus rings) and slower ones for content transitions or page-level changes.</p>

    <table class="">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Token</th><th>Value</th><th>Intended use</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--motion-duration-instant</code></td>
          <td><code>50ms</code></td>
          <td>Micro-feedback — active press states, checkbox ticks</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--motion-duration-fast</code></td>
          <td><code>150ms</code></td>
          <td>Quick feedback — hover highlights, tooltip appearance</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--motion-duration-base</code></td>
          <td><code>250ms</code></td>
          <td>Standard transitions — dropdowns, modals, tab switches</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--motion-duration-slow</code></td>
          <td><code>400ms</code></td>
          <td>Content reveals — page transitions, accordion panels</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--motion-duration-deliberate</code></td>
          <td><code>600ms</code></td>
          <td>Dramatic reveals — hero entrance, onboarding steps</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="heading-l">Easing tokens</h2>
    <p>Five named easings covering every motion scenario. Choosing the right easing for the direction of movement makes animations feel physical and intentional.</p>

    <table class="">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Token</th><th>Value</th><th>When to use</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--motion-easing-linear</code></td>
          <td><code>linear</code></td>
          <td>Continuous loops, spinners, progress bars</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--motion-easing-in</code></td>
          <td><code>cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 1, 1)</code></td>
          <td>Elements <strong>leaving</strong> the screen (starts slow, ends fast)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--motion-easing-out</code></td>
          <td><code>cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1)</code></td>
          <td>Elements <strong>entering</strong> the screen (starts fast, decelerates)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--motion-easing-in-out</code></td>
          <td><code>cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1)</code></td>
          <td>In-place state changes — expanding panels, toggled states</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--motion-easing-spring</code></td>
          <td><code>cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1)</code></td>
          <td>Playful, physical feedback — notification pop-ins, successful actions</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

